### 47. VIEWING THE DISTANT.

<span id="img_tao47"></span>

|                    |
|--------------------|
| ![](img/tao47.jpg) |

1\. "Without passing out of the gate  
The world's course I prognosticate.  
Without peeping through the window  
The heavenly Reason I contemplate.  
The further one goes,  
The less one knows."

2\. Therefore the holy man does not travel, and yet he has knowledge. He
does not see things, and yet he defines them. He does not labor, and yet
he completes.

